What does this CSS produce?

```css
:root {
  --brand: #0066cc;
  --spacing: 16px;
}
.sidebar {
  --brand: #ff6600;  /* local override */
}
.card {
  background: var(--brand);
  padding: var(--spacing, 8px);
}

<!-- HTML -->
<div class="sidebar">
  <div class="card">Card A</div>   <!-- What color? -->
</div>
<div class="card">Card B</div>    <!-- What color? -->
```

What does this CSS produce?

```css
@property --size {
  syntax: '<number>';
  inherits: false;
  initial-value: 1;
}
.box {
  --size: 1;
  width: calc(var(--size) * 100px);
  height: calc(var(--size) * 100px);
  background: #f00;
  transition: --size 0.5s ease, background 0.5s ease;
}
.box:hover {
  --size: 2;
  background: #00f;
}
```
